Sentencas: Atypical operating temperature of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is above 600 degrees C, which leads to severe thermal stresses caused by the difference in material mechanical properties during thermal cycling.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: Interfacial shear stress and peeling stress are the two types of thermal stresses that can cause the mechanical failure of the SOFC.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: Two commonly used SOFC configurations (electrolyte-supported and anode-supported) were considered for this study.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: The paper developed a mathematical model to estimate the thermal stresses and to predict the lifetime of the cell (Ni/8YSZ-YSZ-LSM).
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: Due to the mismatch of the material mechanical properties of the cell layers, a crack nucleation induced by thermal stresses can be predicted by the crack damage growth rate and the initial damage distribution in the interfacial layer for each thermal cycle.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: It was found that the interfacial shear stress and peeling stress were more concentrated near the electrode free edge areas.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: The number of cycles needed for failure decreased with the increase in the porosity of electrode.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: The number of cycle for failure decreased with increase in electrolyte thickness for both anode- and electrolyte-supported SOFC.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions

Sentencas: The model provides insight into the distribution of interfacial shear stress and peeling stress and can also predict damage evolution in a localized damage area in different SOFC configurations.
Titulo: Modeling of thermal stresses and lifetime prediction of planar solid oxide fuel cell under thermal cycling conditions
